    <refbody class="- topic/body        reference/refbody " xtrc="refbody:1;18:14" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">
        <section class="- topic/section " xtrc="section:1;19:18" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">
            
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:1;21:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">On the IBM StoredIQ application stack, a license program writes usage information to
                an IBM Software Licence Metric Tag (SLMT) file. This file has the extension .slmtag
                and can be read periodically by the IBM License Metric Tool (ILMT) after it has been
                configured to scan for these files. You can generate reports that summarize
                usage.</p> 
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:2;26:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">By default, the license program retrieves the size of the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrc="b:1;26:77" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">All Data Objects</b> infoset in terabytes once per day
                and writes this information to the /var/siq/ilmt/3cd1469042433ee7010fe09f661dc67b.slmtag
                file. The .slmtag file can store information up to a maximum file size of 1 MB, after which the file is
                archived and a new log file is created. A maximum of 10 log files are kept.</p> 
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:3;30:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">The .slmtag file contains usage information in the following format, where new metric records are
                appended to the end of the file:</p> 
            <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xml:space="preserve" xtrc="codeblock:1;32:24" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">
                &lt;SchemaVersion&gt;2.1.1&lt;/SchemaVersion&gt;
                &lt;SoftwareIdentity&gt;
                &lt;PersistentId&gt;cb98e260a2a14872902578de1b8e2016&lt;/PersistentId&gt;
                &lt;Name&gt;IBM StoredIQ Data Assessment&lt;/Name&gt;
                &lt;InstanceId&gt;/var/siq/ilmt&lt;/InstanceId&gt;
                &lt;/SoftwareIdentity&gt;
                &lt;Metric logTime="2019-01-25T15:58:26+00:00"&gt;
                &lt;Type&gt;TERABYTE&lt;/Type&gt;
                &lt;SubType&gt;All Data Objects&lt;/SubType&gt;
                &lt;Value&gt;0.005&lt;/Value&gt;
                &lt;Period&gt;
                &lt;StartTime&gt;2019-01-25T15:58:26+00:00&lt;/StartTime&gt;
                &lt;EndTime&gt;2019-01-25T15:58:26+00:00&lt;/EndTime&gt;
                &lt;/Period&gt;
                &lt;/Metric&gt;
            </codeblock>
        </section>
        
        <section audience="novice" class="- topic/section " id="integration_IBM" importance="low" xtrc="section:2;51:74" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:4;52:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrc="b:2;52:19" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">Integration with IBM License Metric Tool</b> </p>
            
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:5;54:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">Versions of IBM License Metric Tool (ILMT) that support IBM Software License Metric
                Tag (SLMT) can generate license consumption reports. An ILMT agent can scan in
                configurable intervals the file system for .slmtag files, collect information, and
                send it to the corresponding ILMT server. ILMT reports the number of terabytes
                managed by IBM StoredIQ. This number is to be used as input for the RVU License
                Conversion Table specified in the license information (li_languagecode file) that
                comes with IBM StoredIQ. On the application stack, you can find the license
                information in the License directory.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:6;62:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita">For more information about using IBM License Metric Tool, see the <xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://www.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SS8JFY_9.2.0/com.ibm.lmt.doc/welcome/LMT_welcome.html" scope="external" xtrc="xref:1;62:224" xtrf="file:/C:/Users/patscully/Dropbox/Current%20Working%20Clients/Information%20Designs%20&amp;%20Development/project_2_ps/workspace/publications/deployment_and_configuration_guide/topics/references/license_usage_metrics.dita"><?ditaot usertext?>IBM License Metric Tool
                documentation.</xref></p>
        </section>
        
        
        
        
